    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Generates a signal for FMCW radar in baseband.</para>
<para>The generated signal consists of three parts, in this order:</para>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>CW part with constant frequency</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Up-chirp</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Down-chirp</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>The up-chirp goes from CW frequency to CW frequency plus sweep frequency and the down-chirp goes in the opposite direction. All of these parts can be disabled by setting the corresponding length to zero.</para>
<para>The packet length for subsequent tagged streams is calculated by the sum of the number of samples of the single modulations parts. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
